ncmpc
------------------------------------------
ncmpc is a curses client for the Music Player Daemon (MPD). ncmpc 
connects to a MPD running on a machine on the local network, and 
controls this with an interface inspired by cplay.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15
  libglib2.0_0-2.18.4-1
  libintl8-0.17-2
  libncurses8-5.5-3
  mpd-0.14.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-1
  automake1.10-1.10.1-2
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.3-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gettext-devel-0.17-2
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.23a-2
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://mpd.wikia.com/wiki/Client:Ncmpc

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/musicpd/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ncmpc-0.13-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ncmpc-0.13-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ncmpc-0.13-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ncmpc-0.13-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/ncmpc.exe
  /usr/share/doc/ncmpc-0.13/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/ncmpc-0.13/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/ncmpc-0.13/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/ncmpc-0.13/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/ncmpc-0.13/README
  /usr/share/doc/ncmpc-0.13/config.sample
  /usr/share/doc/ncmpc-0.13/keys.sample
  /usr/share/doc/ncmpc-0.13/ncmpc.lirc
  /usr/share/man/man1/ncmpc.1.gz

